post_text:
HAPPY TEACHER APPRECIATION WEEK!!

It has taken a while to write this post because the PTO members have heavy hearts. We cannot properly show our teaching staff how much we truly appreciate their hard work, kindness and devotion to our children.

Normally we would shower our beloved teachers with meals, special messages and surprises. This year, it was just not a safe, feasible option, so we had to settle for written praise via email.

We would like to invite all students and/or parents to show your appreciation by posting you thank you notes to your teachers in the comments. (Or email them directly with your words of appreciation.)

THANK YOU TEACHERS! We appreciate everything you continue to do for us.

One of our Aquarists will be ‚Äúdiving‚Äù into our Indo-Pacific exhibit to perform important coral and exhibit maintenance. Our Aquarium Curator, Michelle, will be on hand to answer all of your questions LIVE!

March 15 at 3:59 PM ¬∑

First National Bank and Dairy Queen of Pierre are concerned about the kids and families who will be affected by our schools closing this coming week. School lunch is so important for these kids and we simply cannot let them go without. Many families aren‚Äôt fortunate enough to have extra food in case of an emergency and hopefully we can help reduce the burden these families face. So if you need help, please stop at Dairy Queen of Pierre March 16th through March 20th between 11-2pm each day, for a free kids meal. No questions asked and no purchase necessary. Eligibility rules below.....

‚Ä¢Must be ordered and picked up in drive thru only. We will not serve kids meals in dining room or over the front counter.
‚Ä¢Children 12 and under only
‚Ä¢Child must be present in the car to receive free meal.
‚Ä¢Offer available from 11am-2pm only
‚Ä¢Meal choices from our kids meal menu

post_text: This is amazing! üç¥üíó
shared_text:
Dietitian Liz‚ÄéPierre Governor Grub
January 28 at 11:57 AM ¬∑

The Pierre School District's Food Service Department recently partnered with the Southeast Community Center to feed those in need and reduce food waste. Monday, January 27th, Georgia Morse Middle school kicked off the partnership by donating beef and cheese burritos and corn to SECC.

It is important that every student is fed. It is also important that our left over food not be thrown in the trash. The Food Service Department takes care in estimating the amount of food that needs to be prepared each day but are bound to have some remaining after the lunch period. Our kitchen managers can predict the lunch count fairly accurately and are geniuses when it comes to saving and refreezing certain items for next time. However, many of our products do not freeze and reheat well like the burritos pictured. We want to stop filling trash cans and start filling bellies with our leftovers.

Pictured: Barb Lindbloom (left) Director of SECC and Liz Marso (right) School Foodservice Director

This is amazing! üç¥üíó

Dietitian Liz‚ÄéPierre Governor Grub
January 28 at 11:57 AM ¬∑

The Pierre School District's Food Service Department recently partnered with the Southeast Community Center to feed those in need and reduce food waste. Monday, January 27th, Georgia Morse Middle school kicked off the partnership by donating beef and cheese burritos and corn to SECC.

It is important that every student is fed. It is also important that our left over food not be thrown in the trash. The Food Service Department takes care in estimating the amount of food that needs to be prepared each day but are bound to have some remaining after the lunch period. Our kitchen managers can predict the lunch count fairly accurately and are geniuses when it comes to saving and refreezing certain items for next time. However, many of our products do not freeze and reheat well like the burritos pictured. We want to stop filling trash cans and start filling bellies with our leftovers.

Pictured: Barb Lindbloom (left) Director of SECC and Liz Marso (right) School Foodservice Director

WELCOME TO THE 2019 - 2020 SCHOOL YEAR!

Here is some important information to get all our families ready to go!

New students registering for the first time should register on Tuesday, August 6th at the school and must bring their birth certificate, immunizations, and report card from the school they previously attended.

Registration & School Pictures are on August 12th, 8am - 3pm. Returning students should receive a packet of information in the mail in order to prepare for this.

Kindergarten Parent Night will take place August 15th, 5:30 - 6:30 pm. Parents only please. Kiddos will have plenty of time to prepare at open house.

Open House for EVERYONE will be Monday, August 19th at 5:30 p.m.

SCHOOL STARTS WEDNESDAY, AUGUST 21ST!

We officially have less than a month of summer left. Let‚Äôs enjoy it while we get prepared for the upcoming school year.

post_text: We have exciting news from the Kennedy Elementary PTO! Friday, May 3rd from 6 P.M. to 8:30 P.M we will be having the first Family Prom at Kennedy Elementary. Tickets are $15 for 2 guests or $25 for a family (parents and children) until April 18th. After April 18th the price goes up to $20 for 2 guests and $30 for a family. In addition to dancing and music we will have a light supper (hot dogs and chips), punch,and a silent auction and a raffle (we need donations!). Ticket sales kick off before and after the school concert next Tuesday, March 26th.
